26100:...What was this girl going around cutting and hitting? Did Kozupii seriously do such horrifying stuff like that?\p;
26200:And what about me...? Did I have the power to do that too...?\p;
26300:No... I wasn't special.\n;I wasn't a Gigalomaniac.\p;
26400:And in the end, I hadn't even been able to obtain a DI-sword.\p;
26500:〔Kozue〕“But Takumi-shan <i>s</i><i>a</i><i>w</i> Takumi-shan's sword, riiight?”\p;
26600:〔Kozue〕“You'll get it real soon, Takumi-shan! Kozupii knows it!”\p;
26700:I'm telling you, it's no good... Even back at O-FRONT, it just didn't work... Sure, I did see a sword there, but I had zero clue how to actually grab it...\p;
26800:〔Kozue〕“Weeell, I'm sure if Takumi-shan <i>a</i><i>s</i><i>k</i><i>s</i> how to get it...”\p;
26900:Kozupii peered at Sena as if to urge her to do something.\n;Sena let out another sigh.\p;
27000:〔Sena〕“As biorhythms climb, the \c:255;neurons\c:0; in the midbrain limbic system excessively secrete dopamine, and one's DI-sword appears.”\p;
27100:〔Sena〕“Depending on the person, this could come from feeling threatened, excited, sad, hateful, or happy.”\p;
27200:〔Sena〕“The higher the amount of dopamine secreted, the easier it becomes to observe.”\p;
27300:〔Kozue〕“There you go-sies, Takumi-shan!”\p;
27400:It was just absurd how wide Sena's knowledge was. She might very well be an outright genius.\p;
27500:I mean, with explanations this detailed, you'd think she'd majored in Gigalomaniacology, if that was even a thing.\p;
27600:For starters, I couldn't imagine there being any other girl in all of Japan who could spout theories and jargon off the top of their head to this degree...\p;
27700:Where on God's green Earth had she studied literally any of that?\p;
27800:What was with all the mysterious characters accumulating around me?\p;
27900:I was dying for an answer.\p;
28000:Thinking about it all just wore me out.\p;
28100:It sucked ass only half-understanding what was going on.\p;
28200:But I didn't have the strength to look into it myself.\n;Because... none of these people... were normal in the slightest.\p;
28300:Grappling with those feelings of bitterness, I took one last bite of my thawing Crunchy-kun.\p;
28400:〔Takumi〕“Oh... I won.”\p;
28500:It said “Win!” on what was visible of the stick.\n;Kozupii came back and peered into my hand.\p;
